", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "crop", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "fileId", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "attachToType", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "attachToId", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Creates the thumbnail. Validation and access control must be done prior\nto the invocation of this method."]}, {"name": "girder_thumbnails.worker.attachThumbnail", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "file", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "thumbnail", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "attachToType", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "attachToId", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "width", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "height", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Add the required information to the thumbnail file and the resource it\nis being attached to, and save the documents.\n\n```\nparam file\n\nThe file from which the thumbnail was derived.\n\ntype file\n\ndict\n\nparam thumbnail\n\nThe newly generated thumbnail file document.\n\ntype thumbnail\n\ndict\n\nparam attachToType\n\nThe type to which the thumbnail is being attached.\n\ntype attachToType\n\nstr\n\nparam attachToId\n\nThe ID of the document to attach the thumbnail to.\n\ntype attachToId\n\nstr or ObjectId\n\nparam width\n\nThumbnail width.\n\ntype width\n\nint\n\nparam height\n\nThumbnail height.\n\ntype height\n\nint\n\nreturns\n\nThe updated thumbnail file document.\n```\n"]}, {"name": "girder_thumbnails.worker._getImage", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "mimeType", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "extension", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "data", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Check extension of image and opens it.\n\n```\nparam extension\n\nThe extension of the image that needs to be opened.\n\nparam data\n\nThe image file stream.\n```\n"]}, {"name": "girder_thumbnails.worker.scaleDicomLevels", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "dicomData", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Adjust dicom levels so image is viewable.\n\n```\nparam dicomData\n\nThe image data to be processed.\n```\n"]}, {"name": "girder_thumbnails.worker._scaleIntensity", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "img", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "window", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "level", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "maxc", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Change window and level data in image.\n\n```\nparam img\n\nnumpy array representing an image\n\nparam window\n\nthe window for the transformation\n\nparam level\n\nthe level for the transformation\n\nparam maxc\n\nwhat the maximum display color is\n```\n"]}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}]}